Reason: Old site wasn't really updateable anymore.. the spell lists were totally correct and up to date - up to Velious. All other lists, other than the forum, was worse.<br>
<br>
So: We're moving, to a new site were more accurate info can be maintained, one of those pieces was IMO too good not to repost here:<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro - The Wizard's God<br>
<br>
<br>
Wizards can choose between a variety of religion choices, depending on their race (twelve in all - the most being eight choices for Humans, the least being only one for Frogloks) - but most of these are just piece of crap gods with no value whatsoever, be it roleplayingwise, factionwise, or equipmentwise.<br>
<br>
There’s really only one choice for religion if you’re a wizard: Solusek Ro, the Burning Prince. He is the patron god of Wizards in the same way that Rallos Zek is the patron god of Warriors, Innoruuk is the patron god of Dark Elves, and Quellious is the patron goddess of playing with Barbies. <br>
<br>
Solusek Ro is generally regarded as the God of Fire, Power, and Arcane Knowledge. His actions over the centuries have generally reinforced this view: he certainly enjoys fire and magma, especially when used in an offensive manner (as does any good Wizard); and he has constructed a Temple where his servants, devoted to the pursuit of Power, share valuable knowledge with those who prove their worth.<br>
<br>
The other deities generally have messages that are equally removed from the job description of a Wizard. Wizards are supposed to be the diehard seekers of power and knowledge, at all costs, caring nothing for objects and actions that do not help them attain their goal. Instead, these other dieties clog this spartan and straightforward purpose with excess baggage, like “Save the bunnies!” “Violence isn’t the answer!” and “Puss is sexy!” Not only are most of these messages totally unrelated to the goal of getting magical power, they’re downright unwizardly. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Wizards want to blow stuff up and get a bigger spellbook, not protect the rainforests.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Thankfully, that’s exactly Solusek Ro’s philosophy: blow up anyone who disagrees with you while you actively search for power. His actions over the course of Norrath’s history reflects this mentality. It was the Great Lord Solusek Ro who destroyed the ancient Elven empire on Tunaria (now called Antonica). Their land, once green and vibrant and filled with life, is now the Desert of Ro: three territories of endless rock and sand, inhabited only by venomous spiders and snakes, the undead, and groups of orcs and sand giants. All of Tunare’s creations were forced to flee from what had been their home for centuries, to eke out a new life for themselves on the continent of Faydwer. Such is the punishment of those who draw the ire of the Burning Prince.<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro has also been implicated in the destruction of the ancient Gnomish city of Klik’Anon, and travelers from the Plane of Flames report that he is currently devising a means to turn all of Norrath into a flaming wasteland, with endless pools of lava and a sky choked with ash, with brimstone falling from the heavens rather than rain. The thought of such a world might make you very happy. That’s entirely natural - you’re a Wizard, after all.<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro also wins, hands down, in the faction department. Some Agnostics will try to win you over to the path of godlessness with the “We have better faction argument!” THEY’RE LYING. Agnostic faction is absolutely identical to Solusek Ro faction, with only two exceptions: Solusites are amiably in the Temple of Solusek Ro, and KOS in the Plane of Growth. The Plane of Growth is Tunare’s plane: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>a completely useless crapheap filled with nature-loving hippies</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. If you’re a Dark Elf, you’ll be KOS in the Plane of Growth no matter what you do, so there’s no reason not to worship Solusek Ro!<br>
<br>
The other major argument that the misinformed make against Solusek Ro is that worshiping some other god will get you liked more in your home city. THEY’RE ALSO LYING.<br>
<br>
The Wizard guilds in your home city will like you no matter what god you pick - about the only people who care are the Clerics, and who needs them! For Dark Elves, worshiping Solusek Ro over Innoruuk will get you accepted into parts of many cities that would otherwise beat the grape juice out of you. For Erudites and Gnomes, worshiping Solusek Ro over other, more goody-two-shoes gods will get you accepted with open arms into Neriak and the evil outpost on Kunark, invaluable tools for the intrepid adventurer - and all while keeping your ties to good and neutral cities intact!<br>
<br>
So, a message to all your individuals thinking about making a Wizard - only one god is the God of Wizardry. That god is Solusek Ro, the Burning Prince, Lord of Fire, Keeper of Knowledge, Seeker of Power, and all-around badass.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wxs.nl/~tom.van.der.veen/Sig-custom.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#660066><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub22.ezboard.com/brutabagaparadoxforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alabastureblakmace>Alabasture Blakmace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The dissappearing reappearing<br>.. dissappearing reappearing.. <br>RUTABAGA!<br>(..really, I'm not addicted!)</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/26/03 9:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1081.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Okay, just HAD to repost this one for you guys</span><hr size=1> Haha, cute Ete.  I never saw a reason to worship anyone but Solusek as a Wizard either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#660066><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub22.ezboard.com/brutabagaparadoxforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gvelz>Gvelz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Found The Salad Bar! </span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(2/26/03 10:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub22.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1081.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.fohat.com/gvelz60.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=